The paper deals with locally checkable graph problems in distributed computing, which falls under the category of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also discusses complexity measures such as distance and volume, which are relevant to the sub-categories of cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.IT (Information Theory). The use of bounded-degree graphs and the study of hierarchies suggest that the paper may also be relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
